ASG are free

scaling policies:
manual scaling: you change the values manually
scheduled scaling: where you scale the instances based on time, eg: sales
dynamic scaling: based on cpu memory throughput


lifecycle hooks

asg health checks:
checks the health of below things
ec2 instances: this is default one, instance state is in terminated, shutdown, stopping, stopped or impaired then ec2 will mark instance as unhealthy
loadbalancer: Checks whether the load balancer reports the instance as healthy, confirming whether the instance is available to handle requests.
custom: where instance health is marked as healthy or unhealthy by an external or your custom checks

